WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.920
The Barcelona Game by Stephen Rappley Penguin Active Reading Level 1

00:09.920 --> 00:24.720
Holly Hooper lives in Manchester. She has two brothers, Kev and Trev. Holly is 12, Quiet

00:24.720 --> 00:35.840
and loves books. The boys are 17, noisy and love football.

00:35.840 --> 00:40.320
One September morning, Kev runs into the kitchen.

00:40.320 --> 00:50.320
They're here, he shouts. The tickets for the Barcelona Game are here. He dances across

00:50.320 --> 00:59.120
the kitchen floor. Holly is reading Oliver Twist. She puts her book down.

00:59.120 --> 01:09.760
The Barcelona Game? She asks. What's that? Trev looks at her.

01:10.720 --> 01:19.680
You don't know, he says. Manchester United are playing in Spain on Wednesday.

01:19.680 --> 01:23.120
Dad, Kev and I are going.

01:23.120 --> 01:27.440
Oh, Holly says.

01:27.440 --> 01:36.560
But that evening, Dad isn't well. Next morning, he talks to Kev and Trev.

01:36.720 --> 01:50.640
I'm sorry boys, he says. I've got a bad cold. I can't go to a shoe to Spain with you.

01:52.480 --> 02:01.040
But Dad, we've got three tickets for the aeroplane, Kev says, and three tickets for the game.

02:01.920 --> 02:08.800
And a hotel room for you too, Trev says. What are we going to do?

02:13.200 --> 02:21.360
The room is quiet. Then mum says, I know, you can take Holly.

02:23.200 --> 02:28.400
Kev looks at Trev. Trev looks at Kev.

02:29.280 --> 02:39.600
Yes, Dad says. That's the odds, sir. It is the summer holidays and she's doing Spanish at school too.

02:41.520 --> 02:51.360
But, Kev and Trev say, no buts, mum says, you're taking your little sister with you.

02:51.360 --> 02:56.880
The next day is Wednesday.

02:58.320 --> 03:04.480
Kev, Trev and Holly leave for Spain. Holly is very happy.

03:06.080 --> 03:12.720
On the aeroplane, she reads a book about Barcelona. There are a lot of photos in it.

03:13.040 --> 03:23.440
It's a beautiful place, she thinks. Behind her, the boys are sleeping.

03:24.880 --> 03:29.040
They arrive at Barcelona airport at three o'clock.

03:29.840 --> 03:34.960
Okay, Trev says, let's take a taxi to the hotel.

03:35.920 --> 03:46.880
Then Holly says, oh no, and stops suddenly. She can see a big hole in her bag.

03:46.880 --> 03:51.040
Some of her books are falling on the floor.

03:53.440 --> 04:01.680
Kev looks at Trev. Trev looks at Kev. This is a good start, Kev says.

04:02.000 --> 04:08.960
Then he sees a small airport shop. There are some bags in the window.

04:10.160 --> 04:12.160
They have Barcelona on them.

04:16.000 --> 04:21.600
Go and buy a new bag, he tells Holly. But be quick, okay?

04:23.680 --> 04:31.040
Holly buys one of the Barcelona bags. Then she and her brothers take a taxi to their hotel.

04:32.560 --> 04:38.960
Holly goes into her room. It has two windows and a very big bed.

04:40.640 --> 04:43.360
This is great, she thinks.

04:45.280 --> 04:47.840
Then she goes into Kev and Trev's room.

04:49.600 --> 04:54.000
Okay, what are we going to do before the game? She asks.

04:54.960 --> 05:08.080
We can see the cathedral or the famous street Las Ramblas or the Olympic Stadium or no, no, no.

05:09.040 --> 05:18.000
Kev says, we don't want to go to those places. We're going to Tibidabo. It's a fun fair.

05:18.000 --> 05:25.440
Trev's friend went there in April. It's great, he says.

05:27.440 --> 05:40.000
A fun fair, Holly says. But no buts, Kev says. I'm telling you, it's great. We're going there

05:40.000 --> 05:41.520
and you're coming with us.

05:41.520 --> 05:48.480
Later, Holly and the boys arrive at Tibidabo.

05:50.320 --> 05:57.680
Look, there's a big wheel. Trev says, I love big wheels.

05:59.440 --> 06:03.120
Me too, Kev says. Let's go.

06:03.440 --> 06:11.280
Holly looks at the wheel. Oh, no, she thinks.

06:13.840 --> 06:16.960
Five minutes later, the wheel stops.

06:21.200 --> 06:26.560
That was great, Trev says. Let's do it again.

06:27.200 --> 06:32.480
Then he looks at Holly. Her face is white.

06:34.640 --> 06:36.960
Are you all right? He asks.

06:38.640 --> 06:42.880
No, Holly says. I'm not.

06:45.040 --> 06:49.040
Kev looks at Trev. Trev looks at Kev.

06:49.680 --> 07:02.880
Okay, listen, Kev says. You see that cafe? Go and wait for us there. But stay there and

07:02.880 --> 07:09.680
don't move, okay? Okay, Holly says.

07:09.760 --> 07:17.120
And put the tickets in your bag, Kev says. We don't want to take them with us.

07:20.160 --> 07:26.640
See you at seven o'clock, okay? Yes, Kev, Holly says.

07:28.160 --> 07:32.640
She puts the tickets in her bag. Then she walks to the cafe.

07:32.640 --> 07:41.760
At the cafe, Lamassia, Holly sits down. She asks for coffee.

07:43.280 --> 07:45.840
Then she looks at her Barcelona book.

07:48.480 --> 07:55.520
I wanted to see these places, she thinks. And now I'm not going to see them.

07:56.400 --> 08:01.520
I'm in Spain and I'm only going to see a game of football.

08:03.920 --> 08:06.560
Her coffee comes and she drinks it.

08:08.880 --> 08:13.600
Ten minutes later, a man sits at the next table.

08:15.360 --> 08:23.680
He has a moustache and a brown coat. He has a bag with Barcelona on it.

08:26.080 --> 08:30.080
Holly sees the bag and smiles.

08:31.280 --> 08:34.640
He's got one too, she thinks.

08:35.440 --> 08:38.000
Then she looks at her book again.

08:39.920 --> 08:46.560
The man drinks two black coffees. And after that, he leaves.

08:47.840 --> 08:51.040
Holly closes her book on Barcelona.

08:51.120 --> 08:59.120
Now what, she thinks? It's only six o'clock.

09:01.120 --> 09:06.080
Suddenly, she remembers Oliver Twist and smiles.

09:07.920 --> 09:16.080
Her bag is on the floor. Holly opens it, but then she stops smiling.

09:16.640 --> 09:23.360
A blue shirt, an American newspaper,

09:26.000 --> 09:32.000
an address book with the name Fred Burns on it.

09:33.200 --> 09:36.160
These aren't my things, she thinks.

09:37.120 --> 09:41.360
I don't understand. Where's my book?

09:42.080 --> 09:46.320
Where's my book? Where are the tickets for the...

09:48.160 --> 09:49.920
Then she closes her eyes.

09:51.680 --> 09:56.720
Oh no! The man with the moustache.

09:58.400 --> 10:02.560
This isn't my bag. It's his.

10:05.120 --> 10:10.320
She stands up. Suddenly, her hands are cold.

10:12.160 --> 10:15.600
Where is he? Where is he?

10:17.440 --> 10:22.960
She runs out of the cafe. There are a lot of people in the street.

10:24.080 --> 10:26.080
Holly looks left and right.

10:30.240 --> 10:33.520
I can't see him, she thinks.

10:35.920 --> 10:39.120
A boy on a motorbike is passing the cafe.

10:40.000 --> 10:43.200
He sees Holly's face and stops.

10:44.640 --> 10:47.360
What's wrong? He asks her.

10:49.280 --> 10:50.720
She starts to tell him.

10:52.320 --> 10:54.640
Then, she looks across the street.

10:56.480 --> 10:58.400
A taxi is driving away.

10:59.760 --> 11:02.560
Fred Burns is sitting in the back.

11:04.400 --> 11:06.560
That's him, she shouts.

11:07.520 --> 11:11.280
There he goes. He's got my bag.

11:12.800 --> 11:15.920
Stop! Stop!

11:17.840 --> 11:20.720
He can't hear you, says the boy.

11:21.920 --> 11:23.920
The traffic's very noisy.

11:25.360 --> 11:28.160
Listen. Do you want to follow him?

11:28.800 --> 11:30.800
Holly looks at the boy.

11:32.800 --> 11:36.800
How? On your motorbike?

11:37.520 --> 11:41.280
Yes. Holly thinks about it.

11:43.520 --> 11:46.720
Okay, she says.

11:50.640 --> 11:53.680
The boy gives her a crash helmet.

11:54.640 --> 11:57.280
Put this on, he says.

11:58.960 --> 12:02.160
Holly sits behind him and puts it on.

12:04.720 --> 12:07.440
What's your name? She asks.

12:09.040 --> 12:11.440
Pele, the boy answers.

12:13.120 --> 12:17.120
Then, he starts the bike and drives quickly away.

12:19.520 --> 12:21.600
Holly closes her eyes.

12:22.080 --> 12:26.560
Fred Burns' taxi is yellow and black.

12:29.920 --> 12:34.880
It goes left, right, and left again very quickly.

12:36.320 --> 12:38.160
Pele follows it.

12:39.360 --> 12:41.760
Holly opens her eyes.

12:43.200 --> 12:45.520
They are passing a big building.

12:46.800 --> 12:50.240
She remembers one of the photos in her book.

12:52.000 --> 12:56.560
That's the Olympic Stadium, she thinks.

12:59.760 --> 13:05.360
Ten minutes later, Fred Burns' taxi is in the famous street,

13:05.360 --> 13:06.240
Lusramblas.

13:07.920 --> 13:10.720
Holly can see her bag in the back window.

13:12.080 --> 13:14.000
She can see Fred Burns, too.

13:16.080 --> 13:19.040
Please stop, she thinks.

13:19.680 --> 13:21.600
Where are you going?

13:23.680 --> 13:26.400
There are some traffic lights in front of them.

13:27.440 --> 13:29.600
They go from green to yellow.

13:33.440 --> 13:38.640
The taxi passes the lights, but then the lights go red.

13:40.480 --> 13:44.400
Two old women start to walk across the street.

13:45.280 --> 13:49.040
They have got a lot of flowers in their hands.

13:51.040 --> 13:53.920
Oh, no, Holly says.

13:55.520 --> 13:58.240
She looks at the back of Fred Burns' head.

13:59.600 --> 14:01.520
We can't catch him now.

14:03.440 --> 14:04.560
Yes, we can.

14:05.520 --> 14:06.480
Pele shouts.

14:08.320 --> 14:11.680
He drives in front of the two women very quickly.

14:12.560 --> 14:15.120
One says, ayeee!

14:16.640 --> 14:21.360
Sorry, Pere shouts, and drives away.

14:23.960 --> 14:27.280
Pere follows the taxi for a long time.

14:27.960 --> 14:32.080
Then it stops near Barcelona's famous cathedral.

14:34.920 --> 14:37.040
Holly and Pere stop, too.

14:37.040 --> 14:44.040
stop too. There are a lot of people and cars in front of the cathedral.

14:44.040 --> 14:53.040
It's a beautiful building, Holly thinks. Then she remembers Fred Burns.

14:53.040 --> 15:03.040
Look! There he is, Perry says. He's getting out of the taxi.

15:03.040 --> 15:06.040
Holly takes off her crash helmet.

15:06.040 --> 15:09.040
Stop! She shouts.

15:09.040 --> 15:14.040
Mr. Burns, please stop.

15:14.040 --> 15:20.040
She gets off the bike and starts to run.

15:20.040 --> 15:27.040
Perry watches the English girl. She is running very quickly.

15:27.040 --> 15:32.040
Fred Burns is walking into the cathedral.

15:32.040 --> 15:39.040
The American hears his name and stops.

15:39.040 --> 15:48.040
Me, he says. He looks left and right. Then he sees Holly.

15:48.040 --> 15:53.040
She runs to him and starts talking.

15:53.040 --> 16:02.040
Two minutes later, she comes back to Perry. There is a big smile on her face.

16:02.040 --> 16:07.040
Have you got the right bag now? He asks.

16:07.040 --> 16:13.040
Yes, I have. Holly is very happy.

16:13.040 --> 16:20.040
Oh, Perry, thank you. How can I?

16:20.040 --> 16:24.040
But then she stops smiling.

16:24.040 --> 16:29.040
Oh, no! What time is it?

16:29.040 --> 16:38.040
Perry looks at his watch. 20 to 7. Why?

16:38.040 --> 16:43.040
Suddenly Holly's face is white again.

16:43.040 --> 16:51.040
Kevin Trev. They're going to be at La Masia in 20 minutes.

16:51.040 --> 16:57.040
She tells Perry about her brothers and the football game.

16:57.040 --> 17:02.040
I understand, the Spanish boy says.

17:02.040 --> 17:07.040
Okay, put your helmet on again.

17:07.040 --> 17:12.040
Perry and Holly drive back to La Masia very quickly.

17:12.040 --> 17:17.040
They pass a lot of beautiful old buildings.

17:17.040 --> 17:26.040
This is great, Holly thinks. I'm seeing Barcelona now.

17:26.040 --> 17:33.040
Five minutes later, she and Perry pass the big wheel at Tibidabo.

17:33.040 --> 17:39.040
What time is it now? Holly asks.

17:39.040 --> 17:44.040
One minute to seven, the Spanish boy says.

17:44.040 --> 17:50.040
It's okay. You're not going to be late.

17:50.040 --> 17:53.040
He stops in front of the cafe.

17:53.040 --> 17:56.040
Holly looks at the people there.

17:56.040 --> 18:02.040
Good, she says. Kevin Trev aren't here.

18:02.040 --> 18:06.040
Then she gets off the motorbike.

18:06.040 --> 18:12.040
Perry, how can I thank you? She says.

18:12.040 --> 18:20.040
That's okay. Perry answers. I had a good time.

18:20.040 --> 18:23.040
He looks at his motorbike.

18:23.040 --> 18:27.040
There are two red flowers in one of the wheels.

18:27.040 --> 18:33.040
Here, he says, and he gives the flowers to Holly.

18:33.040 --> 18:37.040
These flowers are for you.

18:37.040 --> 18:44.040
Have a good time at the game. Okay?

18:44.040 --> 18:52.040
He smiles and starts his bike. Then he drives away.

18:52.040 --> 18:56.040
Kevin Trev arrive at the cafe.

18:56.040 --> 19:00.040
Holly is reading Oliver Twist.

19:00.040 --> 19:02.040
She looks up.

19:02.040 --> 19:09.040
Oh, hello, she says. Are we going now?

19:09.040 --> 19:14.040
There are a lot of people in the new camp football stadium.

19:14.040 --> 19:21.040
Trev and Holly get there ten minutes before the game.

19:21.040 --> 19:25.040
Have you got the tickets? Kev asks his sister.

19:25.040 --> 19:32.040
Yes, Holly says, and she takes them from her bag.

19:32.040 --> 19:42.040
The boys buy food and drinks. Then they all sit down.

19:42.040 --> 19:48.040
We had a great time this afternoon. Trev says.

19:48.040 --> 19:54.040
Yes, Kev says, a great time.

19:54.040 --> 20:00.040
Good, Holly says. Me too.

20:00.040 --> 20:06.040
Kev looks at Trev. Trev looks at Kev.

20:06.040 --> 20:11.040
Then they look at their little sister and smile.

20:11.040 --> 20:15.040
You, Kev says.

20:15.040 --> 20:19.040
Holly, you never have.

20:19.040 --> 20:23.040
But the players are coming into the stadium.

20:23.040 --> 20:29.040
United! United! Kevin Trev shout.

20:29.040 --> 20:32.040
Holly looks at them.

20:32.040 --> 20:37.040
Yes, me, she thinks.

20:37.040 --> 20:41.040
I had a great time.

20:41.040 --> 20:43.040
She smiles.

20:43.040 --> 20:49.040
Then she opens Oliver Twist and starts to read.

